Yea, but the point is I don't have to invoke the trigger if I am not doing my own measurements. So really, there is no good way for me to measure myself without impacting the results in some fashion.

Generically what I do in my code is something line:
```
var start = Date.now();
...
...
await ow.trigger.invoke({
  name: "Transaction",
  params: {
    start: start,
    end: Date.now()
  }
 })
return {status: "OK!"}
```
I need to do the await on the invocation otherwise the action might terminate before it has had a chance to post. Though it is an unblocking post.

@rabbah Thank you for going ahead about this. 

> this gets the PR ready for merging.

Can't wait to see that happen.

This is a feature request from an end user that is calling an external API, this API returns JSON as string, and the web action want to return it as is, without the extra penalty of going thru `JSON.parse()`

For example this will work and not give an error by the controller
```
function main() {
  return {
    headers: {
     'Content-Type': 'application/json'
    },
    body: '{"foo":"bar"}'
  }
}
```
